The paper discusses challenges related to security for Industrial Control Systems (ICS) and proposes a gamified approach to address those challenges. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of gamification in education and research, which could also place it in the cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) sub-category. The paper also discusses the evaluation of the proposed approach, which could place it in the cs.SE (Software Engineering) sub-category. The focus on ICS suggests that the paper could also belong to the cs.CY (Computers and Society) sub-category. Finally, the use of an ICS testbed and attacker models suggests that the paper could also belong to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category.
